newsitem.title: SINGAPORE: Singapore oil products gives up earlier gains.
newsitem.headline: Singapore oil products gives up earlier gains.

text.p: Singapore oil product swaps lost most of its gains from Tuesday as the market discounted the possibility of a full blown war in Iraq following the U.S. missile attack, trading sources said.

October gas oil swaps traded down to $27.15 on Wednesday afternoon, about 50 cents below Tuesday's close. On Tuesday, prices rose by about $1.00 following news of the first U.S. missile attack on Iraq.
Brokers said offers were currently seen at a lower $27.10 and buyers have backed down to $26.90.
